<Content>Nice Rooms but Staff Stole Went to Barcelona last Feb/March and the room was clean, if not a little small and we loved the neighborhood. Great small bars throughout the neighborhood that were very friendly, helpful and hospitable. Breakfast was a little spendy but acceptable. Only thing that took away from an above average rating was someone (probably housekeeping) stole 3 shirts from my wife's open suitcase. Which we discovered as we were packing to leave at 4 am and we told mgmt about our missing shirts and they said MAYBE we missed them when packing (didn't because we went thru the room with a find-tooth comb) and then they said maybe we packed them and forgot about it or overlooked it (checked when we got home and NO they were missing). Mgmt did nothing about it after we returned to the States. Very disappointing BUT I loved the city and would tell everyone who has a chance, to please visit!!! 
