<Author>Pimpalicious
<Content>Great Hotel! I have just come back from a 3 night stay at the NH Numancia, I found the hotel to be excellent, it was clean, modern and I found the location to be great.The hotel itself is a five minute walk from the Sants Estacio Metro station, the metrol station is on the green line and I found that most of the tourist attractions are on this line so you are pretty much central to everything. It is also only a 15 minute walk away from the Nou Camp. By staying at this hotel you are not in the hustle and bustle and for me personally I found this a good thing. The area surrounding the hotel is very nice and clean and quiet. There is also a supermarket just across the road which is always helpful.The room was very modern and clean and had everything that you needed. We did not have a view from our window however that did not bother me as you are only really there to sleep!My only concern about the hotel is the restaurant, my boyfriend and I chose to eat there one night as we were feeling pretty tired! Having looked at the menu we thought that due to the types of dishes that were availiable we felt that the food would be up to a high standard. The food was awful!!!! We both ordered the lamb, it was stone cold and when we did complain the waitress did not seem to care or be concerned, I think this was due to the language barrier. It was definitely not worth the 60 Euros that we spent on it!Overall I would recommend this hotel as it is very clean and modern and the location is ideal. 
