<Author>woohoo650
<Content>Pleasantly surprised! My bestfriend and I stayed at NH Numancia Hotel from 11/11/06 - 11/14/06 as part of a package deal from go.com. We were kind of nervous at first since the hotel we stayed at in Madrid turned out to be an apartment and it was in a pretty dirty, sub-par section of the city. We were pleasantly surprised when we arrived at the Numancia hotel. It was clean, the room smelled really nice, and the hotel had a contemporary decor. We arrived early and since our room wasn't ready yet, the bellboy took our luggage and we had lunch nearby. The hotel is centrally located, I would say in the business section, with lots of tapas bars and restaurants around. The Ramblas was a taxi ride away, around 7 euros. The taxi and bus stop were right across the hotel as well as the Metro. The hotel was also located within walking distance from El Corte Ingles (a big shopping chain in Spain) as well as another shopping complex and also some designer stores - a short 2-block walk. The buffet breakfast was fabulous and very filling! The bathroom amenities were great. The room was kept clean by the staff everyday ....spotless. They also provided some Smint mint and also a couple of chocolate squares on the nightstand. I would definitely recommend NH Numancia for the value, cleanliness, and the location. I wouldn't mind staying there again the next time I'm in Barcelona. 
