<Author>lenusik
<Content>Great value, friendly staff Spent 6 nights here. Location: The cab driver knew exactly where it was even though it's not exactly near the La Rambla area. Can walk to railroad station and Espana Square. 3 minutes walk to L3 metro. The bus stop is right in front of the hotel. Close to some shopping and the supermarket. If you like to stay in the middle of the hustle and bustle and crowds don't stay here as you won't be able to walk all the time from the Gothic Quarter and La Rambla here, but if you are OK with the metro then this is very pleasant area.Excellent restaurant at moderate prices which we used a few times at night. Breakfast buffet had all to feed various travelers but nothing truly fancy. Room service claimed to close at midnight but we could not get it at 11pm. However, my feeling was if we went to the lobby we could still get food there. Reception booked an excellent flamenco show and had many kinds of maps. There were always 3-4 people at the reception desk and they were very willing to help with anything from the converter to car rental.Hotel is undergoing renovation right now to expand (April-May 2005) so expect noise at 8:30am during the week. Sat/Sun was quet. 
